	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)">charge to my yr</p>
				<p>Rd Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Be good enough and send to my address an extra weekly marked<lb/> F W&#44; commencing with the first no. x  The <persName>Rd Mr Cohen</persName><lb/> Editor of the Israelitish Volks friend of which I send you a <del>no</del> copy<lb/> is desirous of exchanging with you&#44; price same as yours&#44; if<lb/> you send him the 1. &#38; 2d he will know that you accept his terms<lb/> <persName>Mr. Holzman</persName> of <placeName>Main St</placeName> does not <sic>reve</sic> his papers regularly he wishes<lb/> you to look to it for him.  The enclosed packet is an attempt<lb/> to answer an Ar. In the Israelite of <date>April 1.</date> in which he <persName>D. W</persName> has attacked<lb/> me very much unbecoming a Gentlm. And a minister.  I had written it&#44; with the<lb/> intention of answering him through one of our Daily Papers but my family<lb/> has persuaded me otherways&#44; it is <sic>there</sic> opinion that had <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> meant<lb/> well he should have sent his rejoinder through the Occident&#44; which <sic>offerd</sic><lb/> its papers for that purpose&#44; but he well knows&#44; that there are many<lb/> who read the <del>Occid</del> Israelite never see the Occidt. Thus he has it all his<lb/> own way.  I have  <sic>culld</sic> some of the sentences from some of the Articles<lb/> in the Occidet. <del>thinking</del> as I intended it for a strange paper they the public<lb/> would have had some information regarding the erratic course of the Israelite<lb/> however if you think proper to publish my rejoinder&#44; subject to yr<lb/> correction and then send a few <hi rend="underline">copies</hi> here.  I will get them filed in<lb/> all the reading rooms of this place in company with the Israelite</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We have <sic>finaly</sic> adopted the German Minag it has displaced<lb/> only 2 persons namely <persName>I. Hershberg</persName> and a <persName>Mr. Samuels</persName> <del>who</del> They have <add>&#63;</add><lb/> we can well dispense with them&#44; the former in particular who is <sic>realy</sic> a<lb/> very <sic>quarelsome</sic> disposed man&#44; the majority in these cases will rule<lb/> but the change will greatly increase our members.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I write this at the Bake House where we are now making<lb/> Matses.  <persName>Mr. Hyman Moses</persName> &#38; my self are superintending the<lb/> work which is troublesome it is only 11 years ago that 60 Barrels<lb/> of Flour was more than a sufficient for <placeName>Cincint</placeName> &#38; neighborhood<lb/> and now 360 is not enough&#8212;our small congregation will make at<lb/> least this y<del>or</del>ear 80 Barrels into Matses  I shall have an occasion to<lb/> <del>write</del> write shortly again my rejoinder needs no comment from me as it<lb/> speaks for itself   Respy yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">S Bruel</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><addressee>Rd I Leeser</addressee> <date>8. April 59</date> </p>
		</body>
